The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 09 January is 25,110 (2,906.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 04 January, there were 6,494 new confirmed cases (751.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 28 December, there were 3,378 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 92% (3,116 extra cases).
